        <h4>In this type of task you have to make schedules</h4>
        <h5>• Every row is a task or an activity. In this example, it is activities.<br/>
• In the top row you can see time intervals. Here there are time intervals of an hour. In other tasks it might be weeks or days.<br/>
• Click on the square beside each of the activities. The squares have to be equivelant to the time where the activity has to take place. <br/>
• Some activities can happen at the same time. Other tasks have to happen after each other.<br/>
• Your do not have to use all time intervals.</h5>
        <h6>Try to make a schedule for the school party.</h6>
